GLOBAL DEVELOPMENT RULES

1. DO NOT REBUILD EXISTING SYSTEMS

Do NOT rewrite:

Firebase structure
AI implementation
authentication system
routing
layouts
existing components
existing styling system

Only refine and improve them.

2. REUSE EXISTING LOGIC

Reuse:

current JS utilities
Firebase helper methods
modal components
CSS classes
event listeners
AI functions
existing reusable UI

Avoid:

duplicate functions
duplicate listeners
unnecessary new files

3. PRIORITIZE SYNCHRONIZATION

All exercise/workout/user updates must instantly reflect across:

homepage
session page
library page
summary page
result page
admin dashboard

Especially:

exercise edits
exercise deletion
AI modifications
workout completion
analytics
notifications
user deletion

4. PRESERVE RESPONSIVENESS & BRANDING

Do not break:

mobile responsiveness
desktop responsiveness
spacing consistency
typography consistency
current branding/colors
modal styling
card styling

5. FILE ANALYSIS RULE

Before modifying anything, first analyze:

linked JS files
related Firebase calls
related CSS
shared reusable components
event listeners
localStorage/sessionStorage usage
AI generation logic
chart rendering logic

Do NOT patch blindly.

6. FINAL APP TARGET

The final application should feel:

smooth
synchronized
polished
intelligent
responsive
production-ready

without changing the original architecture.

Before coding:

* explain implementation plan
* explain dependencies
* explain potential conflicts
* then implement step-by-step safely
